\max(|x_1-x_2|,|y_1-y_2|) = \frac{\left|x_1+y_1-x_2-y_2\right|+\left|x_1-y_1-(x_2-y_2)\right|}{2}
a = x_1-x_2
b = y_1-y_2
\max(|a|,|b|)=\frac{|a+b|+|a-b|}{2}
c=|a|, d=|b|
